<div id="review_2264086859" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2264086859" />
    <a title="Colin Mitchell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13983918-colin-mitchell"><img alt="Colin Mitchell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1547899650p2/13983918.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2264086859?book_show_action=true">Jan 23, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Colin Mitchell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Colin Mitchell" href="/user/show/13983918-colin-mitchell">Colin Mitchell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140129601" href="/book/show/1855351.The_Skull_Beneath_The_Skin">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13983918-colin-mitchell?shelf=crime">crime</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2264086859" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9318020594080183805">This story, the second in the Cordelia Gray series, is set in the very Agatha Christie like fictitious island off the Dorset Coast. The gathering was for the performance of Clarissa Lisle in the Duchess of Malfia. Cordelia was responding to the death threat messages received by Clarissa when she is cast into the midst of a murder investigation. <br/><br/>The book is saved by the wonderful descriptive text used by P.D.James reminiscent of the great crime writers of the between wars era.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review2264086859">
  <td colspan="2">
    <div class="updateActionLinks">
