    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3038577232" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3038577232" />
    <a title="tortoise dreams" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/51546630-tortoise-dreams"><img alt="tortoise dreams" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1456768521p2/51546630.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3038577232?book_show_action=true">Nov 10, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="tortoise dreams" class="user" itemprop="url" name="tortoise dreams" href="/user/show/51546630-tortoise-dreams">tortoise dreams</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780446348300" href="/book/show/2854885-the-skull-beneath-the-skin">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3038577232" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18311537387626315326"><i>Young private detective Cordelia Gray is hired to protect a West End actress who&apos;s receiving poison pen letters before events take a turn for the worse.</i><br/><br/><b>Mystery Review:</b> <i>The Skull Beneath the Skin</i> is the second and final Cordelia Gray mystery, following ten years after the first (the archly titled <i>An Unsuitable Job for a Woman</i>). P.D. James (1920-2014) was better known for the 14 or so books of her Superintendent Adam Dalgliesh series, but I feel that James finds a certain comfort and freedom in th</span>
  <span id="freeText18311537387626315326" style="display:none"><i>Young private detective Cordelia Gray is hired to protect a West End actress who's receiving poison pen letters before events take a turn for the worse.</i><br /><br /><b>Mystery Review:</b> <i>The Skull Beneath the Skin</i> is the second and final Cordelia Gray mystery, following ten years after the first (the archly titled <i>An Unsuitable Job for a Woman</i>). P.D. James (1920-2014) was better known for the 14 or so books of her Superintendent Adam Dalgliesh series, but I feel that James finds a certain comfort and freedom in these two books, where her protagonist is a woman. This is not a novel for the impatient, adrenaline junkies, or those easily bored. Deliberately paced, James is in no hurry with her story. The first tragic event doesn't occur until 200 pages in. Descriptions are frequent, detailed, and precise, sometimes going back a hundred years. Told in third person, focusing of course on our detective, but also giving us the point of view of other well-developed characters, many of whom had a reason to be up to no good. This isn't a movie in which the camera follows the action always seeing what's going on, moving the plot forward. Rather this is a film in which the lens pans across the countryside, lingers on a scene, and then focuses on a face reflecting an inner life and inner thoughts. Despite its length, the writing is almost always literate, perceptive, and insightful -- James describes humanity. <i>The Skull Beneath the Skin</i> is not quite as philosophically rewarding as the first book. Although the ending also addresses situational ethics, it is only average, unsurprising, and not quite the necessary payoff for a book that could've been 100 pages shorter. [3★]</span>
  <a data-text-id="18311537387626315326" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

