  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2011942766" />
    <a title="Chris" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6770267-chris"><img alt="Chris" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1417793778p2/6770267.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2011942766?book_show_action=true">Apr 06, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Chris" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Chris" href="/user/show/6770267-chris">Chris</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780684177731" href="/book/show/2762737-the-skull-beneath-the-skin">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6770267-chris?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2011942766" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11081152709767409489">2.5 stars. The first half a 2, SOOOO S-L-O-W. Slow paced suspense novels are ok as long as it builds, this one did not for the first half. The second half was much better &amp; I&apos;d rate it 3 stars. Had a little &quot;And then there were none&quot; vibe to it, although not that good of course.<br/><br/>Cordelia Gray, PI, is hired to be a bodyguard to a fading actress (Clarissa) who has been receiving menacing anonymous letters. Many in Clarissa&apos;s orbit either don&apos;t know of the letters or scoff at them as really being a </span>
  <span id="freeText11081152709767409489" style="display:none">2.5 stars. The first half a 2, SOOOO S-L-O-W. Slow paced suspense novels are ok as long as it builds, this one did not for the first half. The second half was much better &amp; I'd rate it 3 stars. Had a little "And then there were none" vibe to it, although not that good of course.<br /><br />Cordelia Gray, PI, is hired to be a bodyguard to a fading actress (Clarissa) who has been receiving menacing anonymous letters. Many in Clarissa's orbit either don't know of the letters or scoff at them as really being a threat. But her husband has concerns as Clarissa is going to star in a play on a small private island off the coast of England. And so the cast of characters assembles and the games begin. When a murder does occur, we are pulled into the "who done it", and along with Cordelia and the police try to figure out the motive and culprit.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11081152709767409489" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


