        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2949984885" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9921234882283815125">An almost 16 hour audiobook takes you on journey with slowly building tension, intrigue, and horror. It manages to combine wit and exquisite prose with a frank exploration of death AND teach you something about international tax law.<br/>Cordelia Gray is part of a legacy of smart, capable, no nonsense heroines, constantly underestimated because of her age and gender. She&apos;s realistically written with blind spots and heart, and I would totally be her friend.</span>
  <span id="freeText9921234882283815125" style="display:none">An almost 16 hour audiobook takes you on journey with slowly building tension, intrigue, and horror. It manages to combine wit and exquisite prose with a frank exploration of death AND teach you something about international tax law.<br />Cordelia Gray is part of a legacy of smart, capable, no nonsense heroines, constantly underestimated because of her age and gender. She's realistically written with blind spots and heart, and I would totally be her friend.</span>
